 influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Aslaby was born about 1414, in Aislaby, Durham, England, United Kingdom, her father, Sir Thomas Aslaby, was 51 and her mother, Lady Jane Lambert, was 50. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Robert Danby II. She died before 26 June 1475, in her hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1414–Bef 26 June 1475":"umbes 1414–enne 26. juunit 1475","1414–1475":"1414–1475","1398–1474":"1398–1474","1438–Female":"1438–Surnud","1439–1496":"1439–1496","1364–Male":"1364–Surnud","1365–Female":"1365–Surnud","Abt 1414":"umbes 1414","Abt 1439":"umbes 1439","Abt 1438":"umbes 1438","1414":"1414","Aft 1 October 1474":"pärast 1. oktoobrit 1474","1365":"1365","1398":"1398","1475":"1475","1364":"1364","1496":"1496","1474":"1474","Bef 26 June 1475":"enne 26. juunit 1475","1439":"1439","1438":"1438","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Bedale, Yorkshire, England":"Bedale, Yorkshire, England","Aislaby, Stockton-on-Tees district, Durham, England, United Kingdom":"Aislaby, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1414–Bef 26 June 1475":"noin 1414–ennen vuotta 26. kesäkuuta 1475","1414–1475":"1414–1475","1398–1474":"1398–1474","1438–Female":"1438–Kuollut","1439–1496":"1439–1496","1364–Male":"1364–Kuollut","1365–Female":"1365–Kuollut","Abt 1414":"noin 1414","Abt 1439":"noin 1439","Abt 1438":"noin 1438","1414":"1414","Aft 1 October 1474":"1. lokakuuta 1474 jälkeen","1365":"1365","1398":"